==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Separatrix
<hw>Sep`a*ra"trix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>-trices</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>-trixes</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., she that separates.]</ety>
<fld>(Arith.)</fld> <def>The decimal point; the dot placed at the left
of a decimal fraction, to separate it from the whole number which it
follows. The term is sometimes also applied to other marks of
separation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sepawn</ent>⟦br⟧
